    dc:creator "Rizzo, Alexandra E.; Salazar-Vallejo, Sergio I." ;
    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "Hesionidae Grube, 1850 (Annelida: Polychaeta) from South-Southeastern Brazil, with descriptions of four new species" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231426>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231428>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231429>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231430> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231426>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Syllidia amaralae new species. A. Holotype MZUSP 506 with pharynx everted, dorsal view; B. Same, ventral view; C. Same, jaws; D. Position of jaws and stylet on proboscis; E. Paratype MZUSP 505, parapodium 4, posterior view; F. Same, parapodium 12, anterior view; G. Supra-acicular heterogomph falciger neurochaetae; H. Sub-acicular heterogomph falciger neurochaetae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/231426/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231428>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Neogyptis nonatoi new species. A. Paratype MZUSP 385, anterior region in dorsal view, pharynx everted, lateral antennae and tentacular cirri lost; B. Holotype MZUSP 386, anterior region, median antenna lost; C. Same, parapodium 6; D. Same, acicular notochaeta, striated, distally blunt; E. Capillary notochaeta, long, striated, marginally serrated; F. Median capillary notochaeta, with spirally arranged denticles; G. Notochaeta short, curved distally and with serrated coarsely face; H. Simple neurochaeta, distally blunt, marginally serrulated from basal to median portion; I. Heterogomph falciger with long blade, marginally serrulated and distally bidentate; J. Heterogomph falciger with short to median blade, marginally smooth and distally bidentate; K. Geniculate neurochaetae, distally pointed." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/231428/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231429>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Oxydromus lanai new species. A. Holotype MZUSP 491, anterior region, dorsal view; B. Anterior region from an epitokous paratype MZUSP 439, dorsolateral view; C. Paratype MZUSP 436, posterior region, dorsal view; D. Furcate notochaetae, basally serrated near of shorter tine; E. Falciger bidentate with short and narrow blade; F. Falciger bidentate with short to long blade." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/231429/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.231430>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Oxydromus lanai new species. A. Paratype juvenile MZUSP 439 with 8 chaetigers, dorsal view; B. Paratype MZUSP 481, parapodium 1, posterior view; C. Same, parapodium 3, posterior view; D. Paratype MZUSP 493, parapodium 4, posterior view; E. Same, parapodium 9, anterior view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/231430/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

